# patent-ingest

A small, robust submodule to ingest patent PDFs (e.g., downloaded from Google Patents):

- Extract text via Poppler `pdftotext`
- Extract figures as JPG via Poppler `pdftoppm` (guaranteed)
- Parse claims (handles two-column merged claim text patterns)
- Align and diff claims between submitted vs granted versions
- Extract relevant excerpts for downstream analysis

## Install (editable)

```bash
pip install -e .[dev]
```

## CLI

```bash
patent-ingest process --pdf submitted.pdf --out runs --doc-id submitted
patent-ingest process --pdf granted.pdf   --out runs --doc-id granted
patent-ingest compare --submitted runs/submitted --approved runs/granted --out runs/comparison
```

## Outputs

Each processed document creates:

- `text/raw.txt`, `text/normalized.txt`
- `figures/pages/page-0001.jpg ...`
- `figures/selected/figure_page_0002.jpg ...` (auto-selected figure-like pages)
- `meta/claims.json`, `meta/sections.json`, `meta/run_manifest.json`

Comparison creates:

- `meta/claims_diff.json`
- `meta/relevant_excerpts.json`
